{
  "text": "SigB and agr activities are modulated by an exposure to HQNO Fig. 4 shows qPCR measurements of the expression of the genes asp23, fnbA, hld (RNAIII), hla, sarA and gyrB at the exponential growth phase for strains Newbould and Newbould\u0394sigB exposed or not to HQNO. The expression of asp23 and fnbA was evaluated in order to verify the hypothesis that SigB is activated during HQNO exposure. The gene asp23 is a well-known marker for SigB activity as for the gene fnbA, although the transcription of the latter is not exclusively influenced by SigB [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Fig. 4A and 4B show that HQNO at 10 \u03bcg/ml induced SigB activity in strain Newbould, as revealed by significant increases of asp23 and fnbA expression. The effect of HQNO on the expression of asp23 and fnbA was further confirmed with the sequenced strain Newman (data not shown). These results suggest that SigB activity is increased by HQNO.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "7723365",
    "[CITATION_2]": "24754711",
    "[CITATION_3]": "11117841",
